  "text": "Although, the value will no longer normally be used, rather than discarding it, it is copied into a cheap backup storage using the checkpointed register file described in [CITATION_1] . So, if there were an exception or mis-speculation between instruction b and c the value of register r1 could retrieved from the slow checkpointed store. The cost of recovering from speculation by flushing the pipeline or by handling an exception completely amortises any cost due to recovering the old value of r1",
